Russian Cruise Ship Sinks on Volga at Least 88 Missing, 1 Dead

-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 
2011-07-10T14:46:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-10/russian-cruise-ship-sinks-on-volga-at-least-88-missing-1-dead.html
The cruise ship “Bulgaria”
carrying at least 173 passengers sank on  Russia ’s Volga River
killing a woman leaving at least 88 missing, according to
Russia’s Emergency Ministry website.  The rescue operation, which is ongoing, has saved 84
people, the website said. The cruise ship Arabella was able to
rescue 78 people, according to the Tatarstan regional emergency
services website.  The authorities started a criminal investigation into the
accident, according to the website of  The Investigative
Committee of the Russian Federation.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow 
 sbierman1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Will Kennedy  at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net . 